title: Textile, 1850–1863
medium:
Medium: cotton
Technique: printed by engraved roller and block printed
dimensions: H x W: 80 x 33 cm (31 1/2 in. x 13 in.)
description: Ground printed in grey in alternate stripe pattern; one stripe, molette printed in moire effect, is over-printed with scattered rose clusters in pinks and greens. Alternate stripe, probably roller printed, consists of symmetrical pattern of stylized floral motifs and diamond shapes.
